LAGOS  – The Director-General of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Ma­jor-General Shuaibu Ibrahim has promised more commitment to hu­manity in all his future endeavours. He stated this on Saturday in Abuja, during a reception organised for him by the NYSC top management and state coordinators to celebrate his pro­motion to the rank of Major General. Ibrahim, in a statement signed by Emeka Mgbemena, Deputy Director Press and Public Relations, NYSC, at­tributed his achievements in office to the support of the entire NYSC work­force and appealed for more support to attain higher feats. 2023: I’ll Rather Return Home Than Join APC – Senator… NURTW Clashes: Bode George Blames Sanwo-Olu, Says Lagos Island… “Giving to humanity is the best in­vestment someone can leave behind. I feelhighly honoured, lamsohappy and l see myself as a fulfilled man”, he said. The DG appealed to all attendees at the reception to put smiles on people’s faces in their respective positions, no matter how small. He also used the occasion to appeal to members of the National Assembly and the Federal Government for the actualization of the NYSC Trust Fund. In her welcome address, the Direc­tor, Information and Communication Technology, Mrs Christy Uba affirmed that Major General Shuaibu Ibrahim has imprinted his footprints in the an­nals of NYSC history.